  "prompt": "What should I do to learn new language?",
  "response": "Here are some effective ways to learn a new language:\n\n1. Immersion techniques\n- Watch movies/TV shows in target language\n- Listen to podcasts and music\n- Change phone/device language settings\n\n2. Language learning apps\n- Duolingo\n- Babbel\n- Rosetta Stone\n- Memrise\n\n3. Take structured classes\n- Online courses\n- Local language schools\n- University classes\n- Private tutors\n\n4. Practice conversational skills\n- Language exchange websites\n- Language meetup groups\n- Find conversation partners online\n- Practice with native speakers\n\n5. Study methods\n- Flashcards\n- Learn grammar basics\n- Practice reading and writing\n- Use spaced repetition techniques\n\n6. Additional resources\n- Language learning websites\n- YouTube tutorials\n- Language learning podcasts\n- Grammar books and textbooks\n\n7. Consistency tips\n- Set daily learning goals\n- Practice regularly\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Don't be afraid to make mistakes\n\n8. Advanced strategies\n- Travel to countries speaking the language\n- Read books in target language\n- Write journal entries\n- Follow social media in that language\n\nEach person learns differently, so experiment and find methods that work best for you.",
